er through their Hooker line — Ezekiel to Martha Hooker in 1748, James to Abigail Hooker in 1753. The brothers' children grew up first cousins on the Cowles side and third cousins on the Hooker side."},{"number":2,"category":"military","header":"Lieutenant promotion came same month wife died","body":"He was promoted from Ensign to Lieutenant of the 1st Company Trainband 15th Connecticut Militia in May 1772 — the same month his wife Abigail Hooker Cowles died. The personal-and-public events coincided in the heaviest weeks of his life."},{"number":3,"category":"marriage","header":"Lost first wife 1772, remarried widow Mary Bull","body":"Eighteen months after Abigail Hooker Cowles's February 1772 death, he married Mary Bull on 15 November 1773 — widow of William Lewis. The new wife brought stepchildren from her first marriage into the Farmington Cowles household."}],"slug":"james-cowles-1723"},"H00287":{"id":"H00287","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":5,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1736,"month":2,"day":5,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00102","mother_id":"I00132"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 287"},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"},{"short":"Connecticut Town Marriage Records pre-1870 (Barbour Collection)"},{"short":"Find a Grave — Memento Mori Cemetery Farmington CT","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/53048/memento-mori-cemetery"},{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909"}],"death":{"year":1772,"month":2,"day":27,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM254","plot_notes":"Find a Grave memorial — Memento Mori Cemetery"},"marriages":[{"children_ids":["H00613","H00614","H00615","H00616","H00617","H00618","H00619"],"spouse_id":"X00260","marriage_number":1,"date_year":1753,"date_month":8,"date_day":30,"location_city":"Farmington","location_state":"Connecticut","location_county":"Hartford","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1772}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00232","display_label":"Her second cousin Martha married her husband's older brother Ezekiel.","link_text":"Martha Hooker Cowles"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Abigail Hooker Cowles","first_name":"Abigail","last_name":"Cowles","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Cowles"],"gender":"female"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Died at thirty-six leaving seven children","body":"Abigail married James E. Cowles in August 1753 — same Farmington family network that produced her cousin Martha's marriage to James's older brother Ezekiel a decade earlier. She bore seven children between 1754 and 1771 and died at thirty-six in February 1772, eighteen months before her husband remarried Mary Bull."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"She and her cousin married Cowles brothers","body":"Abigail and her second cousin Martha Hooker Cowles married brothers — Abigail to James E. Cowles in 1753, Martha to Ezekiel Cowles a decade earlier. Both Hooker cousins descended from Rev. Samuel Hooker through different sons; both Cowles brothers were sons of Capt. Isaac Cowles by his third wife Elizabeth Smith."}],"slug":"abigail-cowles-1736"},"X00261":{"id":"X00261","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Cowles Family Genealogy"},{"bib_id":"BIB003"},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"},{"short":"Connecticut Town Marriage Records pre-1870 (Barbour Collection)"}],"birth":{"year":1675,"month":3,"day":28,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1756,"month":2,"day":7,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"gender":"male","parents":{"father_name":"Samuel Cowles (1639-1691)","mother_name":"Abigail Stanley Cowles (1637-1734)","father_research_notes":"Samuel Cowles 1639-1691 of Farmington CT (not built). Per WikiTree.","mother_research_notes":"Abigail Stanley Cowles 1637-1734 of Farmington CT (not built). Per WikiTree."},"number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02764","date_year":1694,"date_month":1,"date_day":2,"location_city":"Farmington","location_county":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1708,"children_ids":["X02765","X02768","I00156","X00260"]},{"spouse_id":"X00262","children_ids":["I00156"],"marriage_number":2}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Captain Isaac Cowles","first_name":"Isaac","last_name":"Cowles","title":"Captain","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"marriage","header":"Married two Andrews sisters in succession","body":"His first wife Mary Andrews died July 1705; four years later in November 1709 he married her sister Sarah Andrews. Sarah herself died June 1715 leaving only one infant who had died in 1714 — Isaac married for the third and last time in December 1716 to Elizabeth Smith, twenty-six years his junior.","number":1},{"category":"career","header":"Farmington tailor who became Captain by 1731","body":"A tailor by trade and extensive landholder at Farmington, he rose through the militia ranks — Ensign 1717, Lieutenant 1723, Captain by May 1731 of the 2nd Company Trainband. He also served as Company Clerk in 1714, collector of the minister's rate 1698-1700, constable for several years, and town representative in 1726.","number":2},{"category":"legacy","header":"Five surviving sons divided 2500 pounds, 1763","body":"His will was dated October 1740 and proved March 1756. Seven years later in 1763 his last five surviving sons divided his Farmington estate — approximately £2,500 among themselves as sole heirs, an unusually concentrated inheritance for the colonial period.","number":3}],"slug":"isaac-cowles-1675"},"X02764":{"id":"X02764","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Mary","last_name":"Cowles","maiden_name":"Andrews","married_names":["Cowles"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Mary Andrews Cowles"},"birth":{"year":1674,"month":12,"day":9,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1708,"month":7,"day":19,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X00261","date_year":1694,"date_month":1,"date_day":2,"location_city":